# Backend configuration is supplied to the Lambda as CloudFormation parameters
# at deploy time (see backend/lambda/samconfig.toml → parameter_overrides), not
# via this file. The relevant params are:
#
#   Auth0Domain    — your Auth0 tenant domain, e.g. your-tenant.us.auth0.com
#   Auth0Audience  — your Auth0 API identifier (must match the frontend's
#                    VITE_AUTH0_AUDIENCE)
#   AllowedOrigin  — CORS origin; "*" for dev, your https origin for prod
#   BucketName     — the private sketch bucket name
#   ScriptTokenSecret — long random string used to sign the read-only "script
#                    tokens" baked into a user's Scriptable widget (POST
#                    /me/script-token). Generate with `openssl rand -hex 32`.
#                    Leave blank to disable that endpoint.
#   VapidPrivateKey — base64url VAPID private key used to sign Web Push
#                    notifications to a partner on new sketches. Generate a
#                    keypair once: `pip install py-vapid && vapid --gen`, then
#                    put the *public* key in frontend/.env (VITE_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY)
#                    via `vapid --applicationServerKey`. Leave blank to disable
#                    push notifications.
#   VapidSubject   — contact URI for the VAPID `sub` claim, e.g.
#                    mailto:you@example.com. Required when push is enabled.
#
# The previous shared-secret model (AUTH_SECRET / x-auth-token) has been removed
# in favor of Auth0 JWT verification, so no secret is needed here anymore.
#
# Frontend env vars live in frontend/.env (see frontend/.env.example).
